title: '"When we feel obliged to deny one truth in favor of another (e.g., I love you, I’m mad at you), we sign on to an unceasing project of denial and self-constraint. In contrast, accepting the mind’s ability to encompass many perspectives at once means that we can acknowledge the truth of two apparent opposites and move forward creatively"'
pid: b039e7c4-4652-4efd-86ab-acd9de5eb580
